00:25:11,969 --> 00:25:13,639
[clicking and winding continues]

400
00:25:15,597 --> 00:25:17,177
[softly] <i>It's a very powerful connection,</i>

401
00:25:20,602 --> 00:25:23,652
<i>and that is what photography feels like.</i>

402
00:25:23,731 --> 00:25:25,481
[sighs]

403
00:25:25,566 --> 00:25:26,856
[laughs softly]

404
00:25:27,860 --> 00:25:29,990
[Platon]<i> At the end of it,</i>
<i>you've got the aesthetic.</i>

405
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:31,817
<i>That comes last.</i>

406
00:25:35,617 --> 00:25:37,327
[traditional Greek music playing]

407
00:25:37,411 --> 00:25:41,171
<i>When I came back to Greece,</i>
<i>I came back to my people.</i>

408
00:25:47,921 --> 00:25:52,051
<i>And it was an empowering experience</i>
<i>of finding my feet as a human being.</i>

409
00:25:55,804 --> 00:25:57,144
[whoops]

410
00:25:57,222 --> 00:25:58,772
[more whooping]

411
00:26:01,518 --> 00:26:03,268
[cheering and applauding]

412
00:26:05,939 --> 00:26:08,399
[cheering and clapping continues]

413
00:26:08,484 --> 00:26:10,784
<i>After that, I went back to New York</i>

414
00:26:10,861 --> 00:26:14,161
<i>and I spent a year working</i>
